# Project: Northstar Roofing Dashboard

## Overview
- Project type: Next.js 14 + Supabase business dashboard
- Brand: Northstar Roofing (Roaring Fork Valley)
- Integrations: Trello, QuickBooks Online, Estimator App
- Status: Mock data in use; APIs are scaffolded but not connected

## Mandatory Local Checks (Before Push)
- Always run `npm run dev` to test changes locally before running `npm run build` and pushing to GitHub.
- Always run `npm run dev` and `npm run build` locally before pushing.

## File Structure Reference
- `src/app/` app router pages/layouts
- `src/components/` dashboard UI components
- `src/lib/api/` integration services
- `src/lib/supabase/` Supabase clients
- `src/types/` shared domain types
- `docs/` project documentation

## Key Files
- `src/app/layout.tsx` root layout + metadata
- `src/app/page.tsx` main dashboard route
- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx` core dashboard view
- `src/lib/utils.ts` mock data + helpers
- `src/lib/api/trello.ts` Trello integration service
- `src/lib/api/quickbooks.ts` QuickBooks integration service
- `src/lib/api/estimator.ts` Estimator integration service
- `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` browser Supabase client
- `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` server Supabase client
- `src/types/index.ts` domain types

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript only; keep types in `src/types/`.
- Use inline styles (current UI pattern) unless refactoring styles as a task.
- Add `'use client'` at the top of client components.
- Prefer small, composable components over monoliths.
